     <p class="date">February 22, 2016</p>
     <h3>MSBA Announces Student Citizenship Award Winners</h3>
      <p>Park West is proud to announce Emily Barteaux from Major Pratt School as the Individual Category winner for Region 1 and the Rossburn Collegiate Students from Rossburn Collegiate as the Group Category winner.</p>
      <a href="#dialog2" name="modal" id="modal">Click here for more information.</a></p>
   	  <div id="dialog2" class="window">
        <h3>
        <center>
Manitoba School Boards Association Announces Student Citizenship Award Winners</center>
        </h3>
        <p>The Board of Trustees of Park West School Division hosted their annual Student Citizenship Awards Banquet at the George P. Buleziuk Hall on February 4th, 2016. The Board chose divisional representatives in two categories for submission to the Manitoba School Boards Association (MSBA) for consideration in the regional competition.<br />
<br />

The Manitoba School Boards Association has now provided notification regarding the winners for both the Individual and Group categories last week. Park West is proud to announce Emily Barteaux from Major Pratt School as the Individual Category winner for Region 1 and the Rossburn Collegiate Students from Rossburn Collegiate as the Group Category winner.<br /><br />


Emily and the Rossburn Collegiate students will receive their awards at the MSBA Annual Convention in March. Emily is also one of the six finalists being considered for the Association of Manitoba Municipalities George Harbottle Memorial Award. The winner of this award will be announced at the same awards ceremony in March.<br />
<br />

This is the third year in which students from Park West School Division have been chosen as both the Individual and Group winners. The Board is proud that our students continue to demonstrate a passion for social justice and citizenship.<br />
<br />

The Park West School Division Board of Trustees would like to congratulate both Emily and the students of Rossburn Collegiate for their success as MSBA Student Citizenship award winners.
 
 <center>
<img src="Images/Slider/Citizenship.jpg" width="530" height="399" hspace="10" vspace="5" align="right" /></center>
<img src="Images/Slider/Citizenship2.jpg" width="530" height="399" hspace="10" vspace="5" align="left" /></center>
</p>
<br />
<a href="#"class="close"/>Close</a> </div>

     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     <p class="date">February 19, 2016</p>
     <h3>Treaty Education in Park West</h3>
      <p>A two day in-service was conducted at Waywayseecappo School.</p>
      <a href="#dialog1" name="modal" id="modal">Click here for more information.</a></p>
   	  <div id="dialog1" class="window">
        <h3>
        <center>
Treaty Education in Park West</center>
        </h3>
        <p>A two day in-service was conducted at Waywayseecappo School for all Park West School Division teachers.  The topic for the two days was âWe Are All Treaty Peopleâ.  The session was conducted by the Treaty Relations Commission of Manitoba.<br /><br />

Chief and Council provided some information on local treaties, shared personal stories about their experiences growing up, why teaching treaty to students was important and their knowledge about treaties and indigenous culture.<br /><br />

The teachers also had an opportunity to learn about resources that are available to them in order to help them teach about treaty.  Each school received treaty kits filled with resources.
<br /><br />
The commission also conducted an evening session for the public at the Russell Inn.<br /><br />

The two days provided teachers with an opportunity to learn about treaty, receive some strategies and resources on incorporating treaty teaching into curriculum and provided an opportunity to network with colleagues across the division.  It was a great two days of learning. <br /><br />

A special thanks to the staff of Waywayseecappo School for doing a fabulous job of hosting this event.
 <br />
 
 <center>
<img src="Images/TreatyTrainingCheif.jpg" width="320" height="240" hspace="10" vspace="5" align="right" /></center>
<img src="Images/TreatyTraining 006.JPG" width="427" height="284" hspace="10" vspace="5" align="left" /></center>
</p>
<br />
